|--valign=&quot;top&quot;
|{{flag|Ireland }}||&lt;!--Date started--&gt;||See [[Colombia–Ireland relations]]

* Colombia is represented in Ireland through its embassy in London, United Kingdom.
* Ireland is represented in Colombia through its embassy in [[Mexico City]], Mexico and an honorary consulate in [[Bogotá]].
* The Irish have a long relationship with Colombia dating back to involvement by Irish volunteers in the Colombian wars of independence.

Colombia underwent a dispute with Ireland over the return of three Irish citizens, known as the [[Colombia Three]]. The men were first convicted due to their use of false passports and, after an appeal by the prosecution, of providing training to Colombian guerrillas. They escaped while on bail and the Irish government and media are aware of their presence in Ireland.
