|{{Flagu|Bulgaria }}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;||See [[Bulgaria – Czech Republic relations]]

Diplomatic relations between Bulgaria and Czechoslovakia were established on 27 September 1920, they were severed on 1 June 1939 and were restored on 10 October 1945. On 23 December 1992 Bulgaria recognised the Czech Republic and established diplomatic relations with it at the level of embassies as of 1 January 1993. Bulgaria has an embassy and an honorary consulate in Prague.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.mfa.bg/prague/ Bulgarian embassy in Prague]{{dead link|date=April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt; Czech Republic has an embassy in [[Sofia]] and an honorary consulate in [[Varna]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mzv.cz/sofia |title=Czech Republic embassy in Sofia |publisher=Mzv.cz |date=30 December 2007 |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
