|{{Flagu|Liechtenstein}}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;{{dts|format=dmy|2009-07-13}}||

* Both countries established diplomatic relations in 2009.&lt;ref name=&quot;Liechtenstein1&quot;/&gt;&lt;ref name=&quot;Liechtenstein2&quot;/&gt;
|-
|{{Flagu|Lithuania }}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;{{dts|format=dmy|1922-01-05}}
|
* Both countries re-established diplomatic relations on 9 September 1991.
* Lithuania recognised the Czech Republic after the split of Czechoslovakia on 5 January 1992 and diplomatic relation were established the following day.
* The Czech Republic has an embassy in [[Vilnius]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mzv.cz/wwwo/default.asp?idj=2&amp;amb=86 |title=Czech embassy in Vilnius |publisher=Mzv.cz |date=30 April 2010 |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Lithuania has an embassy in Prague and an honorary consulate in Brno.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://cz.mfa.lt/index.php?-1178104675 |title=Lithuanian embassy in Prague |publisher=Cz.mfa.lt |date= |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Both countries are full members of NATO and of the European Union.
* [http://www.urm.lt/index.php?935026264  Lithuanian Ministry of Foreign affairs: list of bilateral treaties with the Czech Republic (in Lithuanian only)]
|-
|{{Flagu|Luxembourg }}||&lt;!--Start date{{dts|format=dmy|--&gt;
|
* The Czech Republic has an embassy in [[Luxembourg City]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mzv.cz/wwwo/?zu=luxembourg |title=Czech embassy in Luxembourg City (in Czech and French only) |publisher=Mzv.cz |date=30 April 2010 |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Luxembourg has an embassy in Prague.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.ambalux.cz/intro.php |title=Luxembourg embassy in Prague |language={{fr icon}} |publisher=Ambalux.cz |date= |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Both countries are full members of the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development, of the European Union and of NATO.
|-
|{{Flagu|Malta }}||&lt;!--Start date{{dts|format=dmy|--&gt;
|
* The Czech Republic is represented in Malta through its embassy in Rome, (Italy) and through an honorary consulate in [[Valletta]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.czech-malta.com/ |title=Czech honorary consulate in Valletta |publisher=Czech-malta.com |date= |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Malta is represented in the Czech Republic through a non-resident ambassador based in the Foreign Ministry at Valletta.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.foreign.gov.mt/images/files/file/CZECH%20REPUBLIC%20for%20blue%20book.pdf Directions of the Maltese representation in the Czech Republic]&lt;/ref&gt;
* Both countries are full members of the European Union.
|-
|{{Flagu|Netherlands }}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;{{dts|format=dmy|1919-11-13}}
|
* The Czech Republic has an embassy in [[The Hague]] and an honorary consulate in [[Amsterdam]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mzv.cz/wwwo/?zu=hague |title=Czech embassy in The Hague |publisher=Mzv.cz |date=30 April 2010 |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* The Netherlands has an embassy in Prague.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.netherlandsembassy.cz/ |title=Dutch embassy in Prague |publisher=Netherlandsembassy.cz |date= |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Both countries are full members of NATO and of the European Union.
*[http://www.minbuza.nl/binaries/pdf/reizen-en-landen/betrekkingen-met-nederland/tsjechi-.pdf  Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs about the relation with the Czech Republic (in Dutch only)]
|-
|{{Flagu|Poland }}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;||See [[Poland – Czech Republic relations]]

Both countries are full members of the European Union. They share {{convert|796|km|abbr=on}} of common border, which can be crossed anywhere without border control due to the Schengen Agreement.
|-
|{{Flagu|Romania }}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;{{dts|format=dmy|1919-04-06}}
|
* After the splitting of Czechoslovakia, the Czech Republic and Romania established diplomatic relation on 18 December 1992.
* The Czech Republic has an embassy in [[Bucharest]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mzv.cz/bucharest |title=Czech embassy in Bucharest (in Czech and Romanian embassy) |publisher=Mzv.cz |date= |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Romania has an embassy in Prague.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://praga.mae.ro/index.php?lang=en |title=Romanian embassy in Prague |publisher=Praga.mae.ro |date= |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Both countries are full members of NATO and of the European Union.
|-
|{{Flagu|Russia }}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;||See [[Czech Republic – Russia relations]]

The present day relatios between the two countries are at their best, and many agreements have been signed. Russia also has further reduced its oil deliveries to the Czech Republic. The Czech Republic has an embassy in Moscow, and two consulate generals (in [[Saint Petersburg]] and [[Yekaterinburg]]). The Russian Federation has an [[Embassy of Russia in Prague|embassy in Prague]], and two consulate generals in (Brno and [[Karlovy Vary]]).
|-
|{{Flagu|Serbia }}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;1918
|
* The Czech Republic has an embassy in [[Belgrade]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mzv.cz/wwwo/?zu=belgrade |title=Czech embassy in Belgrade (in Czech and Serbian only) |publisher=Mzv.cz |date=30 April 2010 |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Serbia has an embassy in Prague.
* Czech relations with Serbia were usually positive, just like relations between Czechoslovakia and [[Yugoslavia]] (prewar). However, Czech government under administration of Mirek Topolánek decided to recognize Kosovo – the very important issue in Serbian politics.
* [http://www.mfa.gov.rs/Policy/Bilaterala/Czech/index_e.html  Serbian Ministry of Foreign Affairs about relations with the Czech Republic]
|-
|{{Flagu|Slovakia }}||&lt;!--Start date--&gt;{{dts|format=dmy|1993-01-01}}||See [[Czech Republic – Slovakia relations]]

Before 1918, both countries were part of Austria–Hungary, and between 1918 and 1 January 1993, both countries were part of Czechoslovakia.
|-
|{{Flagu|Ukraine }}||&lt;!--Start date{{dts|format=dmy|--&gt;
|
* The Czech Republic has an embassy in [[Kiev]] and 2 general consulates in [[Donetsk]] and [[Lviv]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mzv.cz/wwwo/?zu=kiev |title=Czech embassy in Kiev(in Czech and Ukrainian only) |publisher=Mzv.cz |date=30 April 2010 |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Ukraine has an embassy in Prague, a consulate and an honorary consulate in Brno.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mfa.gov.ua/czechia |title=Ukrainian embassy in Prague (in Czech and Ukrainian only) |publisher=Mfa.gov.ua |date= |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.ukrkonzulat.cz/ |title=Ukrainian consulate in Brno(in Czech and Ukrainian only) |language={{cs icon}} |publisher=Ukrkonzulat.cz |date= |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* During the [[Interwar era]] the Ukrainian province [[Zakarpattia Oblast]] was part of Czechoslovakia.&lt;ref name=&quot;Serhy&quot;&gt;[[Serhy Yekelchyk]] ''&quot;Ukraine: Birth of a Modern Nation&quot;'', [[Oxford University Press]] (2007), ISBN 9780195305463 (page 128-130)&lt;/ref&gt;
|-
|{{Flagu|United Kingdom }}||&lt;!--Start date{{dts|format=dmy|--&gt;||See [[Czech Republic – United Kingdom relations]]

[[Majesty|HM]] Queen [[Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom]] paid a [[state visit]] to the Czech Republic in March 1996.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|title= Outward state visits made by the queen since 1952|url= http://www.royal.gov.uk/output/page4869.asp|publisher=Official web site of the British Monarchy|accessdate= 29 November 2008}}&lt;/ref&gt;
|}

==Americas==
===Brazil===
{{see|Brazilian-Czech relations|Czech Brazilians}}

===Canada===
{{main|Canada – Czech Republic relations}}

Canada has an embassy in Prague. The Czech Republic has an embassy in [[Ottawa]], 2 general consulates (in [[Montreal]] and [[Toronto]]) and 3 honorary consulates (in [[Calgary]], [[Vancouver]] and [[Winnipeg]]).

===Colombia===
{{main|Colombia – Czech Republic relations}}

Colombia is represented in the Czech Republic through its embassy in Vienna (Austria). The Czech Republic has an embassy in [[Bogota]] and 3 consulates (in [[Barranquilla]], [[Cartagena, Colombia|Cartagena]] and [[Medellín]]).&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web | url = http://czech-republic.visahq.com/embassy/Colombia/ | title = Czech Republic Embassy in Colombia | publisher=VisaHQ.com}}&lt;/ref&gt;

===Mexico===
{{main|Czech Republic – Mexico relations}}

Diplomatic relations between then Czechoslovakia and Mexico were established in 1922. Mexico re-recognised Czech independence. The Czech Republic has an embassy in Mexico City and 3 honorary consulates (in [[Monterrey]], [[Guadalajara, Jalisco|Guadalajara]] and [[Tijuana]]).&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mzv.cz/wwwo/?zu=mexico |title=Czech embassy in Mexico City (in Czech and Spanish only) |publisher=Mzv.cz |date=30 April 2010 |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt; Mexico has an embassy in Prague.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.sre.gob.mx/republicacheca/ |title=Mexican embassy in Prague (in Spanish only) |publisher=Sre.gob.mx |date= |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;

===United States===
{{main|Czech Republic – United States relations}}

U.S. President [[Woodrow Wilson]] and the United States played a major role in the establishment of Czechoslovakia on 28 October 1918.

===Uruguay===

The Czech Republic has an embassy in [[Montevideo]] and an honorary consulate in [[Maldonado, Uruguay|Maldonado]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=http://www.mzv.cz/montevideo |title=Czech embassy in Montevideo (in Czech and Spanish only) |publisher=Mzv.cz |date= |accessdate=14 April 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt; Uruguay has an embassy in Prague.

